# Version honesty

## Stable installs

Pin user-facing install examples to the **latest stable tag** (`v2.1.0` as of July 2026):

- Docker: `prest/prest:v2.1.0`
- Go: `go install github.com/prest/prest/v2/cmd/prestd@v2.1.0`

Do not leave install paths on older stable tags while hubs advertise a newer release.

## Unreleased `main`

Features only on `prest/prest` main (not yet tagged) must be labeled:

- `{% hint style="warning" %}` **Requires prest `main` (unreleased)** + PR link
- Never claim they ship in v2.1.0 (or any tag they are not on)

Current main-only work to watch:

- Database query storage / registry — [#980](https://github.com/prest/prest/pull/980)
- TimescaleDB E2E certification — [#988](https://github.com/prest/prest/pull/988)

Claim upgrade/install steps only for tagged releases. See `write-docs` voice do-not-claim.
